records.addlTxt:
Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to COUNT 2; straight time. If revoked, defendant may attend the Day Reporting Center and participate in vocational training.

As to COUNT 2-
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to COUNT 1 AMENDED; straight time. If revoked, defendant may attend the Day Reporting Center and participate in vocational training.

Court STAYED the sentence on COUNT 1 AMENDED and COUNT 2 and placed defendant on probation for 24 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Pay restitution in the amount of $40.00 to be paid to Anthony L. Defendant is not to be discharged from probation until the restitution is paid. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
2) Write a letter of apology to Anthony L. by 9/08/2015 and turnover the letter to the juvenile probation agent to send to the victim;
3) No contact with the victim unless approved by the victim;
4) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment or counseling;
5) Participate in a cognitive intervention program;
6) Vocational programming if not enrolled in school full time;
7) Complete 50 hours of community service as approved by the agent;
8) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
9) Court did not order the DNA sample and waived the surcharge because the sample was not ordered;
10) Maintain absolute sobriety;
11) Random urine screens;

Court ordered any cash bail on deposit to apply towards costs, fees and surcharges.

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
